693
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:16,797
Would you care to join us for dinner ?

694
00:56:16,920 --> 00:56:20,310
[ Skipped item nr. 694 ]

695
00:56:20,440 --> 00:56:24,319
No, uh, thank you.
l have to prepare for tomorrow.

696
00:56:24,440 --> 00:56:29,389
See, l just sit here and look pretty
and she does all the work.

697
00:56:29,520 --> 00:56:33,195
He's very lucky
to have you on his side.

698
00:56:43,600 --> 00:56:45,397
Moe, l can hardly hear you.

699
00:56:45,520 --> 00:56:48,876
l'm at the Baltimore Airport
just boarding a plane to Boston.

700
00:56:49,000 --> 00:56:53,596
Thanks to our friendly London
shoe company, l picked up
quite a trail on Greenhill.

701
00:56:53,720 --> 00:56:57,235
He lived here in Maryland
for eight months. Before that,
in Boston under the name of...

702
00:56:57,360 --> 00:56:59,157
Edgar Greenhill.

703
00:56:59,280 --> 00:57:01,157
- lsn't that his middle name?
- Yeah.

704
00:57:01,280 --> 00:57:04,840
Listen, there's a--
There's a woman here, Selma Hanks,

705
00:57:04,840 --> 00:57:08,549
who died here after
she overdosed on sleeping pills.

706
00:57:08,680 --> 00:57:12,275
And another woman in Boston, who, uh,
well, she's on life-support systems...

707
00:57:12,400 --> 00:57:15,039
after she O.D.'d on something.

708
00:57:15,160 --> 00:57:17,754
And they're both
former lady friends of his.

709
00:57:22,480 --> 00:57:24,755
He fixates on a woman and then--

710
00:57:30,760 --> 00:57:33,752
He won't hurt you now. He needs you.

711
00:57:33,880 --> 00:57:36,838
But, Moe,
he's planning something.

712
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:47,352
Now, look, Jen, you--
You be careful of this guy.

713
00:57:47,480 --> 00:57:52,270
Moe, he had to have been
able to get back upstairs...

714
00:57:52,400 --> 00:57:56,712
to kill his wife
with no one seeing him.

715
00:58:14,680 --> 00:58:16,989
Oh, what did l do right?

716
00:58:17,120 --> 00:58:20,078
Oh, l didn't feel
like being alone tonight.

717
00:58:20,200 --> 00:58:22,509
That bastard.
He's really starting to get to you.

718
00:58:41,760 --> 00:58:43,876
How can l help you?

719
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:48,430
You can't.

720
00:58:59,720 --> 00:59:02,678
Thank you.

721
00:59:02,800 --> 00:59:05,872
Oh, good morning. l want you to
know how l loved being in court.

722
00:59:09,480 --> 00:59:11,391
You did very well.

723
00:59:52,920 --> 00:59:54,797
Excuse me.

724
00:59:54,920 --> 00:59:56,717
- Morning, Emily.
- Hi, Jennifer.

725
00:59:56,840 --> 01:00:00,389
Good morning, Counsellor.
Did we oversleep this morning a little?

726
01:00:02,640 --> 01:00:04,790
And State's Attorney Heath,
is this the original...

727
01:00:04,920 --> 01:00:08,151
of the document
you received in the mail?

728
01:00:08,280 --> 01:00:11,670
-lt is.
-May we mark this Prosecution Exhibit C?

729
01:00:11,800 --> 01:00:14,360
And would you read the contents
into the record, please?

730
01:00:18,640 --> 01:00:20,517
''lt's after 12:00 now.

731
01:00:20,640 --> 01:00:23,552
''He's arranged to be alone
with me in the apartment.

732
01:00:23,680 --> 01:00:26,240
''l am not strong enough
to run away.

733
01:00:26,360 --> 01:00:30,069
''l have given up all hope
or reason to fight back.

734
01:00:30,200 --> 01:00:34,910
But if David succeeds, l pray
he will not go unpunished.''

735
01:00:35,040 --> 01:00:38,077
And it's signed,
''Rita Elizabeth Greenhill.''

736
01:00:38,200 --> 01:00:40,077
What did you do after that, sir?

737
01:00:40,200 --> 01:00:42,794
- We sent it to the Criminal
lnvestigation Division...
- Something bothering you today?

738
01:00:42,920 --> 01:00:45,070
-of the State Attorney's Office.
-Sure. The expression...

739
01:00:45,200 --> 01:00:47,111
- on the jury.
- And they, in turn,
sent it to be authenticated.

740
01:00:47,240 --> 01:00:51,199
-And it was therefore verified--
-Don't worry about it.
Diangelo just shot his load.

741
01:00:51,320 --> 01:00:53,914
That letter's all he's got.

742
01:00:58,760 --> 01:01:02,036
One painter's cap.

743
01:01:03,120 --> 01:01:06,351
One dust mask filter.

744
01:01:06,480 --> 01:01:09,597
And one pair of work gloves.

745
01:01:09,720 --> 01:01:12,553
- That is 54.19.
- Okay.

746
01:01:12,680 --> 01:01:14,159
- ls that cash or charge?
- Cash, please.

747
01:01:14,280 --> 01:01:15,429
Okay.

748
01:01:19,080 --> 01:01:21,310
Good morning, Mr Loo.
l thought Mr Greenhill and l...

749
01:01:21,440 --> 01:01:23,715
could, uh, ride
downtown together.

750
01:01:23,840 --> 01:01:26,149
Oh, Mr Greenhill
wasn't here last night.

751
01:01:26,280 --> 01:01:28,271
But he asked me to put out
his clothes...

752
01:01:28,400 --> 01:01:31,915
because he might want to change
before going to court.

753
01:01:32,040 --> 01:01:34,998
- Uh, do you mind if l wait?
- Oh, no, please, feel free.

754
01:01:35,120 --> 01:01:36,917
Care for coffee? l have some made.

755
01:01:37,040 --> 01:01:40,430
- Uh, uh, l prefer tea.
- Of course.

756
01:01:40,560 --> 01:01:42,357
Thank you.

757
01:02:23,600 --> 01:02:25,079
What are you doing?

758
01:02:50,560 --> 01:02:52,949
Quite a responsibility
taking care of all this.

759
01:02:53,080 --> 01:02:57,676
Oh, yes, indeed. Well, Mr Greenhill
is not so, uh, demanding to work for...

760
01:02:57,800 --> 01:03:00,268
now that Mrs Greenhill is gone.

761
01:03:00,400 --> 01:03:04,359
She, uh, she never gave
a person a minute's peace.

762
01:03:04,480 --> 01:03:07,950
- Tea, right?
- Um, actually, no, l'm late.

763
01:03:08,080 --> 01:03:11,755
Would you tell Mr Greenhill
l'll meet him at court? Thank you.

764
01:03:29,040 --> 01:03:31,634
Well, this is a surprise.

765
01:03:36,440 --> 01:03:38,829
Great, we'll split a cab.

766
01:03:38,960 --> 01:03:41,633
- Don't you need to change?
- Don't l look all right?

767
01:03:42,920 --> 01:03:44,717
Excuse me.

768
01:03:52,040 --> 01:03:54,031
The way you were looking at me,
l thought there was somethin' wrong.

769
01:03:54,160 --> 01:03:57,197
A little 5:00 shadow, perhaps, but...

770
01:03:57,320 --> 01:04:00,835
nothing that would turn the jury
against me, do you think?

771
01:04:08,760 --> 01:04:12,036
You know, for the life of me, l can't
figure out who sent that damn thing.

772
01:04:12,160 --> 01:04:16,233
- What?
- The letter, Jennifer.

773
01:04:16,360 --> 01:04:19,557
l mean, they say it was sent
on the same day that Rita died.

774
01:04:19,680 --> 01:04:22,194
But Rita never left
the apartment that day.

775
01:04:22,320 --> 01:04:26,552
And the mail chute upstairs has been
out of use since the renovations began.

776
01:04:26,680 --> 01:04:30,150
Well, you certainly wouldn't
mail any letter to the State's
Attorney's Office yourself.

777
01:04:30,280 --> 01:04:32,077
Of course not.

778
01:04:32,200 --> 01:04:36,751
Suppose the greedy nephew, uh,
sent it or one of the cousins.

779
01:04:36,880 --> 01:04:40,634
They certainly know
what her signature looks like.
They've seen it on enough cheques.

780
01:04:42,000 --> 01:04:44,753
Could l see a photostat
of the envelope?

781
01:05:01,000 --> 01:05:04,117
Sure. Somebody ought
to be able to figure out...

782
01:05:04,240 --> 01:05:07,630
which branch of the post office
this was processed at.

783
01:05:10,120 --> 01:05:12,190
You will follow up on that.

784
01:05:12,320 --> 01:05:14,117
Of course.

785
01:05:16,680 --> 01:05:20,275
According to the postmark,
this letter was picked up somewhere...

786
01:05:24,520 --> 01:05:28,035
Since there was an earlier
pickup at 2:00, the letter
had to have been mailed...

787
01:05:31,480 --> 01:05:34,517
- Objection. Argumentative.
- Rephrase, Miss Haines, rephrase.

788
01:05:34,640 --> 01:05:39,794
By making an even greater enlargement
l was able to make a closer examination.

789
01:05:39,920 --> 01:05:43,310
The-- The loops and
the angle of the letters...

790
01:05:43,440 --> 01:05:46,432
now convince me
it is clearly a fake.

791
01:05:46,560 --> 01:05:49,472
l apologize to the court.

792
01:05:49,640 --> 01:05:52,029
Will counsel approach the bench?

793
01:05:57,560 --> 01:06:01,109
What do you have to say
about this, Mr Diangelo?

794
01:06:01,240 --> 01:06:04,312
Well, we've had our own people
examine the signature again,

795
01:06:04,440 --> 01:06:06,510
and they now tend to agree.

796
01:06:06,640 --> 01:06:09,871
We'll stipulate
it's not her handwriting.

797
01:06:23,400 --> 01:06:25,038
Winning.
l'm talking about...

798
01:06:25,160 --> 01:06:28,038
nailing that fucking Greenhill to
the wall and his lawyer along with him.

799
01:06:28,160 --> 01:06:30,435
Well, after that fiasco with
the forged letter, l would like that.

800
01:06:30,560 --> 01:06:33,597
l got a phone call from one
of his girlfriends yesterday.

801
01:06:37,400 --> 01:06:40,358
- She might have been in on it with him.
- She tipped us where to look:

802
01:06:40,480 --> 01:06:43,358
behind the radiator in the basement
of Greenhill's own building.

803
01:06:43,480 --> 01:06:45,516
We got the search warrant.
Pay dirt.

804
01:06:45,640 --> 01:06:50,111
All the reports are back from the lab.
And there's no question.

805
01:06:50,240 --> 01:06:54,074
David Greenhill
was wearing this stuff.

806
01:06:54,200 --> 01:06:57,636
You're already under oath,
Lieutenant.

807
01:06:57,760 --> 01:07:00,194
- Why are they recalling him?
- l have no idea.

808
01:07:00,320 --> 01:07:02,390
Detective Martinez, would you go
to the exhibits table, please,

809
01:07:12,200 --> 01:07:15,397
Some coveralls that used
to be white at one time.

810
01:07:17,040 --> 01:07:20,191
A pair of work gloves.

811
01:07:20,320 --> 01:07:24,359
A cap similar to that used
by a painter or plasterer.

812
01:07:25,840 --> 01:07:28,912
A gauze face mask used
to filter out dust and debris.

813
01:07:29,040 --> 01:07:33,238
May we admit these as Prosecution
Exhibits D, E, F and G?

814
01:07:33,360 --> 01:07:36,796
And upon obtaining a warrant,
Lieutenant, did you search
Mr Greenhill's apartment,

815
01:07:36,920 --> 01:07:38,876
and did you find
something of interest?

816
01:07:39,000 --> 01:07:42,117
Yes. A pair of
Trevor-Norton shoes...

817
01:07:42,240 --> 01:07:46,392
with the residue of plaster and
paint on the soles of the shoes.

818
01:07:46,520 --> 01:07:50,957
Mark those Prosecution Exhibit H.
Where were the shoes found?

819
01:07:54,600 --> 01:07:57,876
- Did you make an analysis
of the plaster?
- We did.

820
01:07:58,000 --> 01:07:59,797
- And what did you find?
- Are those your shoes?

821
01:07:59,920 --> 01:08:03,549
lt was similar in every way
to the plaster and other
construction materials being...

822
01:08:09,240 --> 01:08:11,595
- No.
- No more questions.

823
01:08:11,720 --> 01:08:13,517
Let him get it all out.

824
01:08:13,640 --> 01:08:15,949
We tested the inside of the cap
for traces of human hair.

825
01:08:16,080 --> 01:08:18,958
Did you compare your findings
to samples of David Greenhill's hair?

826
01:08:19,080 --> 01:08:22,834
Objection. Prosecution made no request
for specimens of David Greenhill's hair!

827
01:08:22,960 --> 01:08:25,394
With all due respect,
Your Honour. We didn't need to.

828
01:08:25,520 --> 01:08:28,432
The investigating officer
found a comb and a brush
belonging to the defendant...

829
01:08:28,560 --> 01:08:30,357
and we took the specimen
hairs from that.

830
01:08:30,480 --> 01:08:34,155
The specimens seemed to have been
acquired under a legal warrant.
l suggest we continue.

831
01:08:35,760 --> 01:08:38,035
Did you do similar tests
on the gauze mask?

832
01:08:38,160 --> 01:08:39,957
We found minuscule particles
of human blood...

833
01:08:40,080 --> 01:08:42,594
such as might be left if
the wearer had recently shaved.

834
01:08:46,000 --> 01:08:48,514
The University of Chicago
prepared these charts.

835
01:08:48,640 --> 01:08:52,713
Entered as Exhibits l
and J for the Prosecution.
Will you explain the chart, please?

836
01:08:52,840 --> 01:08:56,515
The skin sample matches exactly
the defendant's DNA patterns.

837
01:08:56,640 --> 01:08:59,677
- Did you put the gloves
through your spectrograph?
- Examination of the lining...

838
01:08:59,800 --> 01:09:03,156
of the gloves showed traces
of an over-the-counter cleaning
product called Windex Spray.

839
01:09:03,280 --> 01:09:05,271
ldentical to the solvent
present on the window...

840
01:09:05,400 --> 01:09:07,436
through which Mrs Greenhill
was thrown to her death.

841
01:09:07,560 --> 01:09:10,199
- Objection, Your Honour!
- Sustained.

842
01:09:14,520 --> 01:09:18,115
We'll take lunch now.

843
01:09:18,240 --> 01:09:21,437
- Go have lunch.
- We have to talk.

844
01:09:21,560 --> 01:09:23,516
You heard me.

845
01:12:01,560 --> 01:12:03,516
l brought you a sandwich.

846
01:12:03,640 --> 01:12:06,074
Oh, how thoughtful.

847
01:12:06,200 --> 01:12:09,317
Based on what's happened,
do you care to change your plea?

848
01:12:12,440 --> 01:12:14,396
l'll sleep on it.

849
01:12:23,760 --> 01:12:28,151
- What is it?
- Hello, David. Do you know who this is?

850
01:12:31,560 --> 01:12:33,357
Yes. How are things in Boston?

851
01:12:33,480 --> 01:12:37,314
There's been someone around asking
questions about you the last few days.

852
01:12:37,440 --> 01:12:40,238
Of course,
l didn't tell him anything.

853
01:12:41,840 --> 01:12:43,990
An older man?

854
01:12:44,120 --> 01:12:47,908
Seventy? Wears a hat?

855
01:12:51,840 --> 01:12:55,674
Looks like you're going
to lose this one. Thank God.

856
01:12:55,800 --> 01:12:58,872
Let's celebrate.
Call me when you get in.

857
01:12:59,000 --> 01:13:01,833
l'll be home.

858
01:13:01,960 --> 01:13:04,076
l love you, Jennifer.

859
01:14:55,640 --> 01:14:58,712
- Jen.
- l'm right here, sweetheart.

860
01:14:58,840 --> 01:15:02,719
- l'm right here.
- l couldn't see--

861
01:15:02,840 --> 01:15:05,274
l couldn't see who.

862
01:15:21,920 --> 01:15:26,357
This is David's way
of saying he knows.

863
01:15:55,320 --> 01:15:58,232
Ooh! l'm sorry.

864
01:15:58,360 --> 01:16:01,750
- Who were you expecting?
- You know who.

865
01:16:01,880 --> 01:16:04,758
How is he?
ls he gonna be all right?

866
01:16:04,880 --> 01:16:06,677
Yeah.

867
01:16:06,800 --> 01:16:08,870
Can you leave now?

868
01:16:11,040 --> 01:16:15,875
There's somethin' at the office.
l gotta show it to ya. lt's important.

869
01:16:19,800 --> 01:16:24,078
Ya see, it's a clear pattern
but not conclusive proof.

870
01:16:24,200 --> 01:16:26,395
Nothing to make
a prima facie case.

871
01:16:26,520 --> 01:16:28,909
Well, they sure know
where to look.

872
01:16:29,040 --> 01:16:32,476
Well, you divulge any of
those facts and he goes on trial
for any of the other crimes,

873
01:16:32,600 --> 01:16:35,433
they'll throw the cases right out
for violation of confidentiality.

874
01:16:35,560 --> 01:16:40,634
l can't turn him in either,
because, well, l'm employed by you.

875
01:16:40,760 --> 01:16:44,878
- Jury's gotta convict now.
- Well, ya never know.

876
01:16:45,000 --> 01:16:47,958
But as long as that bastard's
out on bail, you--

877
01:16:48,080 --> 01:16:50,514
You watch your step.

878
01:16:54,840 --> 01:16:57,195
l've made my decision.

879
01:16:58,360 --> 01:17:01,113
We'll stick with
the not guilty plea.

880
01:17:01,240 --> 01:17:03,196
That's your call.

881
01:17:04,800 --> 01:17:08,190
Yeah, l didn't want
to do this, but...

882
01:17:08,320 --> 01:17:10,436
now l have no choice.

883
01:17:15,440 --> 01:17:18,512
Mrs Bigelow, say hello
to my attorney, Jennifer Haines.

884
01:17:18,640 --> 01:17:23,794
- How do you do?
- Say hello to Mrs Bigelow.

885
01:17:23,920 --> 01:17:27,708
How is Mrs Bigelow
gonna help us?

886
01:17:29,480 --> 01:17:34,395
Well, her husband isn't
going to like this, but, uh,

887
01:17:34,520 --> 01:17:38,115
well, Kathleen, why don't
you tell Miss Haines...

888
01:17:38,240 --> 01:17:41,915
where l was on the afternoon
of my wife's death?

889
01:17:44,440 --> 01:17:49,036
At my place, just around the
corner from his own apartment.

890
01:17:49,160 --> 01:17:51,435
A five-minute walk.

891
01:17:51,560 --> 01:17:55,792
Naturally l didn't say
anything about it before...

892
01:17:55,920 --> 01:17:58,559
because Kathleen's marriage
was at stake.

893
01:17:58,680 --> 01:18:02,753
And l didn't think there was
much of a case against me.

894
01:18:02,880 --> 01:18:05,269
David was still there when we heard
the police and the ambulance sirens.

895
01:18:05,400 --> 01:18:08,472
He couldn't possibly have had
anything to do with it.

896
01:18:08,600 --> 01:18:11,512
And, tell Miss Haines what
we were doing the week before.

897
01:18:14,360 --> 01:18:19,992
Yes. Um, my eldest daughter
is moving back in with me,
so l've been doing some redecorating.

898
01:18:20,120 --> 01:18:23,430
Slapping on some paint,
putting up some wallpaper, and, uh,

899
01:18:23,560 --> 01:18:26,233
l got David to pitch in and help.

900
01:18:26,360 --> 01:18:29,352
Shamed him into it, actually,
just so he couldn't turn me down--

901
01:18:29,480 --> 01:18:32,597
You got him the proper
clothing to wear?

902
01:18:32,720 --> 01:18:36,508
You got him a cap and gloves?

903
01:18:36,640 --> 01:18:38,119
The painters had left
some things behind when...

904
01:18:38,240 --> 01:18:40,390
they did the upper floor
of the duplex last year.

905
01:18:40,520 --> 01:18:43,557
Mrs Bigelow, you realize
l am obligated...

906
01:18:43,680 --> 01:18:46,752
not to present perjured
testimony to the court?

907
01:18:46,880 --> 01:18:52,318
Excuse me, Jennifer, how can
you be so sure that Kathleen's
not telling the truth?

908
01:18:54,920 --> 01:18:59,914
You must know the State's
Attorney's Office will attempt
to impeach this testimony.

909
01:19:00,040 --> 01:19:03,396
Lady, my husband is a lineman
with the Chicago Bears.

910
01:19:03,520 --> 01:19:07,559
Do you honestly think l'd
jeopardize myself for a lie?

911
01:19:07,680 --> 01:19:10,353
This is a very difficult thing
for me to do,

912
01:19:10,480 --> 01:19:12,869
but David's life is in danger.

913
01:19:17,640 --> 01:19:20,473
All right,
